1
00:00:03,738 --> 00:00:07,174
(Minseok) ⟨I was chased out of a South Korean chaebol family after being accused of embezzlement→

2
00:00:07,241 --> 00:00:11,679
In despair, I met Momoko, a doctor at the clinic⟩

3
00:00:11,746 --> 00:00:15,182
⟨And our hearts connected...⟩

4
00:00:15,249 --> 00:00:18,185
(Momoko) There are trees that won't fall even if you cut them 10 times.

5
00:00:18,252 --> 00:00:21,188
I'm sorry, but I really want to break up with you.

6
00:00:21,255 --> 00:00:23,190
(Minseok) ⟨Suddenly we broke up⟩

7
00:00:23,257 --> 00:00:25,192
⟨Behind that...⟩

8
00:00:25,259 --> 00:00:28,195
(Eri) His mother closed down a hotel in Tokyo→

9
00:00:28,262 --> 00:00:30,197
I'm planning to cut out Minseok.

10
00:00:30,264 --> 00:00:33,200
Please, please break up with him.

11
00:00:33,267 --> 00:00:37,204
(Minseok) I want to protect the people I care about with my power.

12
00:00:37,271 --> 00:00:40,207
⟨For the future with Momoko →

13
00:00:40,274 --> 00:00:42,710
And to protect the hotel →

14
00:00:42,777 --> 00:00:46,781
Just when I was about to face my mother and brother in Korea...⟩

15
00:00:49,784 --> 00:00:51,285
>> Korean

16
00:01:00,294 --> 00:01:02,229
(Mizushima) Welcome.

17
00:01:02,296 --> 00:01:04,165
Please prepare a room for the chairman and president.

18
00:01:05,166 --> 00:01:08,102
What happened today...

19
00:01:08,169 --> 00:01:09,603
Ha!

20
00:01:09,670 --> 00:01:11,605
I'll take you to the lounge, so hurry to your room.

21
00:01:11,672 --> 00:01:14,308
Yes… Yes.

22
00:01:14,675 --> 00:01:16,610
Korean

23
00:01:16,677 --> 00:01:20,181
(Mizushima) Hurry up! Hurry up...

24
00:01:23,684 --> 00:01:25,619
Please guide me to the lounge.

25
00:01:25,686 --> 00:01:27,121
Korean

26
00:01:27,188 --> 00:02:02,156
♪～

27
00:02:02,223 --> 00:02:04,091
No contact from the head office →

28
00:02:04,158 --> 00:02:07,595
The chairman and president will visit →

29
00:02:07,661 --> 00:02:09,663
Is it a surprise check?

30
00:02:11,031 --> 00:02:14,969
Did the deputy manager really not know anything?

31
00:02:15,035 --> 00:02:18,973
(Eri) [Your mother-in-law wanted to banish you from Fangeum→

32
00:02:19,039 --> 00:02:21,542
I'm going to destroy Fangum Hotel Tokyo]

33
00:02:23,043 --> 00:02:25,045
(Mizushima) Deputy manager?

34
00:02:26,547 --> 00:02:28,482
(Minseok) Hotels in Tokyo are →

35
00:02:28,549 --> 00:02:30,985
We are actively working to improve sales →

36
00:02:31,051 --> 00:02:33,487
No worries. >> But...

37
00:02:33,554 --> 00:02:37,558
(Minseok) Let's welcome customers as usual with confidence.

38
00:02:43,063 --> 00:02:44,999
(Minseok) Ha.

39
00:02:45,065 --> 00:02:47,067
(chime)

40
00:02:50,571 --> 00:02:52,506
(Minseok) I would like to speak with the chairman.

41
00:02:52,573 --> 00:02:55,009
>>The chairman is busy, so I can't pass it on to you.

42
00:02:55,075 --> 00:02:58,012
Please pick it up.

43
00:02:58,078 --> 00:03:00,514
(Minseok) I'm your son.

44
00:03:00,581 --> 00:03:03,017
My mother has something important to tell me.

45
00:03:03,083 --> 00:03:04,952
please.

46
00:03:05,019 --> 00:03:07,021
>> Please pick it up.

47
00:03:10,024 --> 00:03:11,525
(locking sound)

48
00:03:14,528 --> 00:03:16,463
(Mika) Please excuse me. (Momoko) Thank you for your hard work.

49
00:03:16,530 --> 00:03:18,032
>>Thank you for your hard work.

50
00:03:19,533 --> 00:03:22,469
(Sound of door opening and closing)

51
00:03:22,536 --> 00:03:31,979
♪～

52
00:03:32,046 --> 00:03:36,550
Korean

53
00:03:42,056 --> 00:03:43,991
(Minseok) Ha.

54
00:03:44,058 --> 00:03:45,559
📱(vibration sound)

55
00:03:50,064 --> 00:03:53,000
(Momoko's voice) "I'm sorry for saying something terrible."

56
00:03:53,067 --> 00:03:54,568
📱(vibration sound)

57
00:03:56,070 --> 00:03:58,072
(Momoko's voice) "I'm waiting."

58
00:04:02,576 --> 00:04:04,945
(sound of door opening)

59
00:04:05,012 --> 00:04:07,448
(Minseok) Thank you for your hard work.

60
00:04:07,514 --> 00:04:10,017
>>Did you talk to the chairman?

61
00:04:11,518 --> 00:04:13,454
(Minseok) No, not yet.

62
00:04:13,520 --> 00:04:16,957
>> Sigh…｡

63
00:04:17,024 --> 00:04:18,959
Night raid, morning rush.

64
00:04:19,026 --> 00:04:21,462
(Minseok) Huh?

65
00:04:21,528 --> 00:04:25,032
>> Have you ever heard of it? Night raid, morning rush.

66
00:04:26,533 --> 00:04:28,469
(Minseok) Sorry, what do you mean?

67
00:04:28,535 --> 00:04:32,473
>>This is a phrase often used by newspaper reporters when conducting interviews.

68
00:04:32,539 --> 00:04:35,476
Someone you can't listen to face-to-face during the day→

69
00:04:35,542 --> 00:04:39,480
Visiting them before going to work or after returning home to interview them.

70
00:04:39,546 --> 00:04:45,486
The point is, if it doesn't work the first time, change the time and meet as many times as you like!

71
00:04:45,552 --> 00:04:49,490
I guess that means...

72
00:04:49,556 --> 00:04:54,561
I think your strength is your tenacity.

73
00:05:01,068 --> 00:05:02,569
(Minseok) Thank you.

74
00:05:18,018 --> 00:05:19,953
(Minseok) Is this the room?

75
00:05:20,020 --> 00:05:21,455
(Staff) Yes.

76
00:05:21,522 --> 00:05:23,957
(Minseok) I'll take your place. >> But...

77
00:05:24,024 --> 00:05:28,462
(Minseok) As the deputy manager, I will be responsible for the delivery.

78
00:05:28,529 --> 00:05:30,464
>> Well then.

79
00:05:30,531 --> 00:05:33,033
(chime)

80
00:05:40,541 --> 00:05:42,042
Korean

81
00:07:19,506 --> 00:07:20,941
(locking sound)

82
00:07:21,008 --> 00:07:33,954
♪～

83
00:07:34,021 --> 00:07:37,524
Korean

84
00:07:51,538 --> 00:07:55,042
(Minseok) [I don't know where the grave is]

85
00:08:09,056 --> 00:08:10,557
📱(vibration sound)

86
00:08:15,729 --> 00:08:18,232
(Takuto's voice) "Do you have time now?"

87
00:08:24,238 --> 00:08:25,739
(Takuto) Yay!

88
00:08:27,474 --> 00:08:30,911
Is it okay raw? (Minseok) Ah, I don't have alcohol today...

89
00:08:30,978 --> 00:08:32,913
(Takuto) What's the matter? You're in a bad mood.

90
00:08:32,980 --> 00:08:34,915
Then I'll drink.

91
00:08:34,982 --> 00:08:36,984
Well, I've already been drinking.

92
00:08:42,489 --> 00:08:44,925
(Takuto) Oolong tea? (Minseok) Ah, yes.

93
00:08:44,992 --> 00:08:47,427
(Takuto) Excuse me, just one oolong tea. (Salesperson) Yes.

94
00:08:47,494 --> 00:08:49,930
(Takuto) Oh, and plum crystal! (Salesperson) Yes.

95
00:08:49,997 --> 00:08:52,432
(Takuto) Minchok, you've never eaten it, have you? Plum crystal.

96
00:08:52,499 --> 00:08:54,434
(Minseok) Plum crystal?

97
00:08:54,501 --> 00:08:58,438
(Takuto) Momoko doesn't like umeboshi, so I couldn't always order it.→

98
00:08:58,505 --> 00:09:01,942
Actually, I love plum crystal.

99
00:09:02,009 --> 00:09:06,446
Look, we have perfect taste.

100
00:09:06,513 --> 00:09:07,948
(Minseok) Yes.

101
00:09:08,015 --> 00:09:10,951
(Salesperson) Sorry to have kept you waiting. It's plum crystal. (Takuto) Hello.

102
00:09:11,018 --> 00:09:13,954
Try it!

103
00:09:14,021 --> 00:09:16,456
It's okay.

104
00:09:16,523 --> 00:09:18,525
(Minseok) Itadakimasu.

105
00:09:22,529 --> 00:09:25,966
(Takuto) Hehehe... Isn't it great?

106
00:09:26,033 --> 00:09:30,470
Don't you feel like your head clears up when you eat something sour?

107
00:09:30,537 --> 00:09:33,040
Something like that would blow up.

108
00:09:34,975 --> 00:09:36,977
Something must have happened.

109
00:09:38,478 --> 00:09:39,913
(Minseok) Eh.

110
00:09:39,980 --> 00:09:42,416
(Takuto) Is it work? Is it Momoko?

111
00:09:42,482 --> 00:09:45,419
Ah, if it's about the clinic, don't worry.

112
00:09:45,485 --> 00:09:48,488
Momoko's guy is doing his best right now.

113
00:09:50,490 --> 00:09:52,926
I heard that Mincheok did a lot of research for me.

114
00:09:52,993 --> 00:09:54,928
About the subsidy system.

115
00:09:54,995 --> 00:09:56,430
Thank you.

116
00:09:56,496 --> 00:09:59,499
(Minseok) No, it was good.

117
00:10:01,501 --> 00:10:04,504
(Takuto) Hey, do you have other things to worry about?

118
00:10:06,506 --> 00:10:09,943
Well then, do you go for some exercise once in a while?

119
00:10:10,010 --> 00:10:13,447
Do you feel refreshed? Then jog →

120
00:10:13,513 --> 00:10:16,450
Boxing catch is also good.

121
00:10:16,516 --> 00:10:20,020
I'm telling you, I can do anything.

122
00:10:22,522 --> 00:10:24,958
What is it?

123
00:10:25,025 --> 00:10:27,461
(Minseok) A long time ago, both my father and brother →

124
00:10:27,527 --> 00:10:30,030
I thought he was playing catch with me.

125
00:10:31,531 --> 00:10:33,533
(Takuto) I see.

126
00:10:35,469 --> 00:10:39,406
Hey, who is the father who raised me in Korea?

127
00:10:39,473 --> 00:10:44,411
You were originally good friends with Minchok's Japanese father, right?

128
00:10:44,478 --> 00:10:48,415
(Minseok) Apparently they were best friends from their school days.

129
00:10:48,482 --> 00:10:51,918
(Takuto) Haven't you heard anything about your Japanese father?

130
00:10:51,985 --> 00:10:53,420
(Minseok) Huh?

131
00:10:53,487 --> 00:10:55,922
(Takuto) Something like when you had an accident.

132
00:10:55,989 --> 00:10:58,425
I don't even know where the grave is.

133
00:10:58,492 --> 00:11:00,994
They didn't even attend a funeral, right?

134
00:11:03,497 --> 00:11:05,432
(Minseok) Um...

135
00:11:05,499 --> 00:11:08,935
(Takuto) Ah, well, am I hearing something strange?

136
00:11:09,002 --> 00:11:11,938
Sorry, sorry... (Minseok) Ah, no.

137
00:11:12,005 --> 00:11:14,441
(Takuto) It's nothing.

138
00:11:14,508 --> 00:11:16,943
Okay, let's eat then→

139
00:11:17,010 --> 00:11:19,946
I guess I'll just go with this plum crystal after all.

140
00:11:20,013 --> 00:11:21,948
(Minseok) Yeah...｡

141
00:11:22,015 --> 00:11:26,520
(Takuto) Hmm, sour! Yummy! Sour but delicious!

142
00:11:30,524 --> 00:11:31,958
(knock)

143
00:11:32,025 --> 00:11:34,895
(Momoko) Yes.

144
00:11:34,961 --> 00:11:36,897
(Kyoko) Do you want to eat ice cream?

145
00:11:36,963 --> 00:11:40,400
(Momoko) Hmm... Good.

146
00:11:40,467 --> 00:11:43,904
>>It's Momoko's favorite crispy chocolate one.

147
00:11:43,970 --> 00:11:46,973
(Momoko) Yeah, no.

148
00:11:50,477 --> 00:11:52,479
>> What happened?

149
00:11:53,980 --> 00:11:55,982
(Momoko) I can't help it.

150
00:11:59,486 --> 00:12:01,988
(Momoko) I'm not sure what to do...

151
00:12:08,495 --> 00:12:10,931
(Momoko) Thank you as always.

152
00:12:10,997 --> 00:12:13,433
>> Eh, wait a minute...

153
00:12:13,500 --> 00:12:15,502
feel ill.

154
00:12:17,003 --> 00:12:19,940
(Momoko) My sister is →

155
00:12:20,006 --> 00:12:24,945
The feeling of always wishing for my happiness →

156
00:12:25,011 --> 00:12:27,514
That's amazing.

157
00:12:29,516 --> 00:12:33,019
>> Eh~ What? that.

158
00:12:35,455 --> 00:12:40,894
(Momoko) Continuing to wish for the happiness of others →

159
00:12:40,961 --> 00:12:45,899
Isn't it more difficult than being happy yourself?

160
00:12:45,966 --> 00:12:49,903
that's why….

161
00:12:49,970 --> 00:12:52,405
Until now, my sister →

162
00:12:52,472 --> 00:12:55,475
I thought he was doing something amazing.

163
00:12:57,978 --> 00:13:00,480
I finally understood.

164
00:13:03,984 --> 00:13:06,920
(Momoko) What the hell?

165
00:13:06,987 --> 00:13:09,923
>> Grow up!

166
00:13:09,990 --> 00:13:12,425
(Momoko) No, stop it! >> I won't stop!

167
00:13:12,492 --> 00:13:14,928
(Kazami) That's too bad.

168
00:13:14,995 --> 00:13:17,430
(Takuto) It's okay, even about the satellite hospital →

169
00:13:17,497 --> 00:13:20,934
I couldn't help you, so I have to do this.

170
00:13:21,001 --> 00:13:25,438
(Kazami) Takuto-kun, you look just like me back then.

171
00:13:25,505 --> 00:13:27,941
(Takuto) Huh? The teacher and I?

172
00:13:28,008 --> 00:13:29,442
>>Yes.

173
00:13:29,509 --> 00:13:31,444
(Takuto) That must be some kind of mistake.

174
00:13:31,511 --> 00:13:36,383
>> Community-based medical care and management of large hospitals.

175
00:13:36,449 --> 00:13:40,387
A young doctor struggles between dreams and reality.

176
00:13:40,453 --> 00:13:43,390
It's the same old me.

177
00:13:43,456 --> 00:13:47,394
(Takuto) Were you involved in the management of a major hospital?

178
00:13:47,460 --> 00:13:50,897
>> Actually, I'm the same as Takuto →

179
00:13:50,964 --> 00:13:53,400
He's the son of a major hospital worker.

180
00:13:53,466 --> 00:13:55,902
(Takuto) Huh! >> Hehe.

181
00:13:55,969 --> 00:13:59,906
In the past, it was because of my parents →

182
00:13:59,973 --> 00:14:03,910
I went to various big hospitals and studied →

183
00:14:03,977 --> 00:14:08,481
The experience I had back then is still useful today.

184
00:14:10,483 --> 00:14:13,920
(Takuto) Is it possible that you are a teacher?

185
00:14:13,987 --> 00:14:17,924
But do you know anyone at the general hospital?

186
00:14:17,991 --> 00:14:19,993
>> Yes, but.

187
00:14:21,494 --> 00:14:23,496
(Takuto) There's something I'd like to find out.

188
00:14:34,007 --> 00:14:37,444
>> Korean

189
00:14:42,949 --> 00:14:45,952
(Minseok) Thank you for your hard work. (Natsume) Thank you for your hard work.

190
00:14:47,454 --> 00:14:49,389
(sound of trotting back)

191
00:14:49,456 --> 00:14:51,458
(Natsume) Did you see it?

192
00:14:53,460 --> 00:14:55,395
(Minseok) Sorry.

193
00:14:55,462 --> 00:14:58,398
>>This is...

194
00:14:58,465 --> 00:15:02,402
Actually, there are rumors.

195
00:15:02,469 --> 00:15:04,404
(Minseok) Rumor?

196
00:15:04,471 --> 00:15:07,907
>> The chairman and president suddenly visited Japan →

197
00:15:07,974 --> 00:15:11,978
I suspect there will be a large-scale restructuring in the near future.

198
00:15:13,980 --> 00:15:16,916
We just had a daughter →

199
00:15:16,983 --> 00:15:20,420
I can't afford to lose my job...

200
00:15:20,487 --> 00:15:23,423
(Minseok) It's okay.

201
00:15:23,490 --> 00:15:25,492
Don't worry.

202
00:15:34,434 --> 00:15:39,439
>> Korean

203
00:16:36,930 --> 00:16:48,441
♪～

204
00:16:57,951 --> 00:16:59,386
(Momoko) Can you see anything?

205
00:16:59,452 --> 00:17:01,388
Oh!

206
00:17:01,454 --> 00:17:03,456
Hello.

207
00:17:05,458 --> 00:17:07,394
Aren't you going to come in?

208
00:17:07,460 --> 00:17:10,397
>> No...

209
00:17:10,463 --> 00:17:12,465
(Momoko) Please come up.

210
00:17:13,967 --> 00:17:18,905
This is everyone's big house.

211
00:17:18,972 --> 00:17:20,974
please.

212
00:17:23,977 --> 00:17:25,412
(Momoko) I'm home.

213
00:17:25,478 --> 00:17:27,914
(Tatsuru) Ah, Momo-chan-sensei!

214
00:17:27,981 --> 00:17:30,417
Welcome back. >> Mr. Momo-chan, nice timing.

215
00:17:30,483 --> 00:17:32,419
It's just been completed.

216
00:17:32,485 --> 00:17:35,855
(Momoko) Hey, everyone, some amazing people came today!

217
00:17:35,922 --> 00:17:37,857
(Children) Huh?

218
00:17:37,924 --> 00:17:39,926
(Momoko) Please.

219
00:17:41,928 --> 00:17:43,863
>> Oh!

220
00:17:43,930 --> 00:17:47,367
(Child) It's my sister! (Child) Next door is great!

221
00:17:47,434 --> 00:17:49,369
I'll bother you.

222
00:17:49,436 --> 00:17:51,371
Welcome, welcome!

223
00:17:51,438 --> 00:17:53,873
(Child) Next door is great! (Eri) Yeah.

224
00:17:53,940 --> 00:17:56,376
Put this in your pocket.

225
00:17:56,443 --> 00:17:59,379
When I turned it over...

226
00:17:59,446 --> 00:18:01,381
(Chica) I made a heart! >>Did you do it?

227
00:18:01,448 --> 00:18:03,383
Yay!

228
00:18:03,450 --> 00:18:06,386
Eri-chan looks nice.

229
00:18:06,453 --> 00:18:08,888
(Momoko) Yes.

230
00:18:08,955 --> 00:18:12,959
>> I hope Minseok comes again.

231
00:18:14,461 --> 00:18:16,396
(Momoko) Yes.

232
00:18:16,463 --> 00:18:31,911
♪～

233
00:18:31,978 --> 00:18:34,981
(Minseok) Thank you for your hard work. >> Thank you for your hard work.

234
00:18:43,990 --> 00:18:46,426
Deputy Administrator.

235
00:18:46,493 --> 00:18:47,994
(Minseok) Yes.

236
00:18:49,996 --> 00:18:52,432
>>Haha.

237
00:18:52,499 --> 00:18:57,437
You haven't forgotten about spinach, have you?

238
00:18:57,504 --> 00:18:58,938
(Minseok) Huh?

239
00:18:59,005 --> 00:19:02,008
>>Report Contact Consultation.

240
00:19:04,010 --> 00:19:07,514
You're not carrying this alone, are you?

241
00:19:10,517 --> 00:19:14,521
Were you able to talk to the chairman?

242
00:19:20,026 --> 00:19:21,961
No matter what the relationship is →

243
00:19:22,028 --> 00:19:24,964
We're all in the same boat →

244
00:19:25,031 --> 00:19:27,033
We're friends.

245
00:19:29,536 --> 00:19:32,472
Ah... bro...

246
00:19:32,539 --> 00:19:36,910
Although calling them friends may be an exaggeration.

247
00:19:36,976 --> 00:19:39,913
In any case, to the deputy manager →

248
00:19:39,979 --> 00:19:44,484
There are many things I haven't taught you yet!

249
00:19:46,486 --> 00:19:48,488
I won't forgive you if you run away.

250
00:19:51,491 --> 00:19:53,493
(Minseok) Manager.

251
00:19:55,995 --> 00:19:59,999
For accepting me here...

252
00:20:03,503 --> 00:20:05,438
(Minseok) Thank you.

253
00:20:05,505 --> 00:20:20,954
♪～

254
00:20:21,020 --> 00:20:22,522
>> Korean

255
00:20:42,976 --> 00:20:47,413
(Momoko) [Minseok-san also wants to create a place where someone can feel safe.]

256
00:20:47,480 --> 00:20:50,483
[Such a dream must never come true]

257
00:20:55,488 --> 00:20:57,924
>> [You want to make customers smile, right? ]

258
00:20:57,991 --> 00:21:01,928
(Y/N) [You can't give up on what you really want]

259
00:21:01,995 --> 00:21:12,505
